        <h3>About Visual Studio</h3>
        <p>
            The visual studio is a tool to develop visual basic program. It comes with two flavors, the community edition and the professional edtion.
            The comunity edition is free to use and is enough for completing this course. The professional version requires a purchase or subscriptions.
            The only thing you need to start using visual studio community editon is a Microsoft account. Your school email has been registered as a Microsoft account already. To sign in, the account is simply your email and the password is your email password.
            You can login to the visual studio using your Microsoft account upon launching or you can sign in later using the button located on the upper right corner of the tool window after launching.
            The text book is based on visual studio community version 2017. However, you can also use version 2019, the changes are minor. 
            If you cannot installed the visual studio on your own computer. You can always use the lab machines in the classroom to complete the homework and the project. All lab machines are preloaded with visual studio 2019. 
            <br><strong>Note</strong>: We only talk about how to use visual studio and develop visual basic programs on Windows. Please do not download and install the visual studio on other operating systems. Again, you can use lab machines for homework and projects.
            This is a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iWoVC3GGMgU&amp;t=223s" ,="" target="_blank">video tutorial</a> shows how to download visual studio 2017 and configure it for visual basic. 
        </p>
